_cpi_offset.description: Current-law values are zero; reforms that introduce indexing with chained CPI would have values around -0.0025 beginning in the year before the first year policy parameters will have values computed with chained CPI.
_cpi_offset.notes: See April 2013 CBO report entitled 'What Would Be the Effect on the Deficit of Using the Chained CPI to Index Benefit Programs and the Tax Code?', which includes this: 'The chained CPI grows more slowly than the traditional CPI does: an average of about 0.25 percentage points more slowly per year over the past decade.' <https://www.cbo.gov/publication/44089>
_cpi_offset.title: Decimal offset ADDED to unchained CPI to get parameter indexing rate

_FICA_ss_trt.description: Social Security FICA rate, including both employer and employee.
_FICA_ss_trt.title: Social Security payroll tax rate

_SS_Earnings_c.description: Only individual earnings below this maximum amount are subjected to Social Security (OASDI) payroll tax.
_SS_Earnings_c.notes: This parameter is indexed by the rate of growth in average wages, not by the price inflation rate.
_SS_Earnings_c.title: Maximum taxable earnings (MTE) for Social Security

_SS_Earnings_thd.description: Wages and self-employment income above this threshold are subjected to Social Security (OASDI) payroll tax in addition to earnings below the maximum taxable earnings threshold.
_SS_Earnings_thd.title: Additional Taxable Earnings Threshold for Social Security

_FICA_mc_trt.description: Medicare FICA rate, including both employer and employee.
_FICA_mc_trt.title: Medicare payroll tax rate

_AMEDT_ec.description: The Additional Medicare Tax rate, _AMEDT_rt, applies to all earnings in excess of this excluded amount.
_AMEDT_ec.title: Additional Medicare tax earnings exclusion

_AMEDT_rt.description: This is the rate applied to the portion of Medicare wages, RRTA compensation and self-employment income exceeding the Additional Medicare Tax earning exclusion.
_AMEDT_rt.title: Additional Medicare tax rate

_SS_thd50.description: The first threshold for Social Security benefit taxability: if taxpayers have provisional income greater than this threshold, up to 50% of their Social Security benefit will be subject to tax under current law.
_SS_thd50.section_2: Threshold For Social Security Benefit Taxability 1
_SS_thd50.title: Threshold for Social Security benefit taxability 1

_SS_percentage1.description: Under current law if their provisional income is above the first threshold for Social Security taxability but below the second threshold, taxpayers need to apply this fraction to both the excess of their provisional income over the first threshold and their Social Security benefits, and then include the smaller one in their AGI.
_SS_percentage1.irs_ref: Form 1040, line 5b, instructions (Social Security Worksheets, line 2 & 13)
_SS_percentage1.title: Social Security taxable income decimal fraction 1

_SS_thd85.description: The second threshold for Social Security taxability: if taxpayers have provisional income greater than this threshold, up to 85% of their Social Security benefit will be subject to tax under current law.
_SS_thd85.section_2: Threshold For Social Security Benefit Taxability 2
_SS_thd85.irs_ref: Form 1040, line 5a&b, calculation (Worksheet, add line 10 values to line 8).
_SS_thd85.title: Threshold for Social Security benefit taxability 2

_SS_percentage2.description: Under current law if their provisional income is above the second threshold for Social Security taxability, taxpayers need to apply this fraction to both the excess of their provisional income over the second threshold and their social security benefits, and then include the smaller one in their AGI.
_SS_percentage2.irs_ref: Form 1040, line 5b, instructions (Social Security Worksheets, line 15)
_SS_percentage2.title: Social Security taxable income decimal fraction 2

_ALD_StudentLoan_hc.description: This decimal fraction can be applied to limit the student loan interest adjustment allowed.
_ALD_StudentLoan_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount will be (1-Haircut)*StudentLoanInterest.
_ALD_StudentLoan_hc.title: Adjustment for student loan interest haircut

_ALD_SelfEmploymentTax_hc.description: This decimal fraction, if greater than zero, reduces the employer equivalent portion of self-employment adjustment.
_ALD_SelfEmploymentTax_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*SelfEmploymentTaxAdjustment.
_ALD_SelfEmploymentTax_hc.title: Adjustment for self-employment tax haircut

_ALD_SelfEmp_HealthIns_hc.description: This decimal fraction, if greater than zero, reduces the health insurance adjustment for self-employed taxpayers.
_ALD_SelfEmp_HealthIns_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*SelfEmployedHealthInsuranceAdjustment.
_ALD_SelfEmp_HealthIns_hc.title: Adjustment for self employed health insurance haircut

_ALD_KEOGH_SEP_hc.description: Under current law, contributions to Keogh or SEP plans can be fully deducted from gross income.  This haircut can be used to limit the adjustment allowed.
_ALD_KEOGH_SEP_hc.title: Adjustment for contributions to either KEOGH or SEP plan haircut

_ALD_EarlyWithdraw_hc.description: Under current law, early withdraw penalty can be fully deducted from gross income. This haircut can be used to limit the adjustment allowed.
_ALD_EarlyWithdraw_hc.title: Adjustment for early withdrawal penalty haircut

_ALD_AlimonyPaid_hc.description: Under pre-TCJA law, the full amount of alimony paid is taken as an adjustment from gross income in arriving at AGI. This haircut can be used to change the deduction allowed.
_ALD_AlimonyPaid_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*AlimonyPaid.
_ALD_AlimonyPaid_hc.title: Adjustment for alimony-paid haircut

_ALD_AlimonyReceived_hc.description: Under pre-TCJA law, none of alimony received is taken as an adjustment from gross income in arriving at AGI. This haircut can be used to change the deduction allowed.
_ALD_AlimonyReceived_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*AlimonyReceived.
_ALD_AlimonyReceived_hc.title: Adjustment for alimony-received haircut

_ALD_EducatorExpenses_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of educator expenses that can be deducted from AGI.
_ALD_EducatorExpenses_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*EducatorExpenses.
_ALD_EducatorExpenses_hc.title: Deduction for educator expenses haircut

_ALD_HSADeduction_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of a taxpayer's HSA deduction that can be deducted from AGI.
_ALD_HSADeduction_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*HSA_Deduction.
_ALD_HSADeduction_hc.title: Deduction for HSA deduction haircut

_ALD_IRAContributions_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of IRA contributions that can be deducted from AGI.
_ALD_IRAContributions_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*IRA_Contribution.
_ALD_IRAContributions_hc.title: Deduction for IRA contributions haircut

_ALD_DomesticProduction_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of domestic production activity that can be deducted from AGI.
_ALD_DomesticProduction_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*DomesticProductionActivity.
_ALD_DomesticProduction_hc.title: Deduction for domestic production activity haircut

_ALD_Tuition_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of tuition and fees that can be deducted from AGI.
_ALD_Tuition_hc.notes: The final adjustment amount would be (1-Haircut)*TuitionFees.
_ALD_Tuition_hc.title: Deduction for tuition and fees haircut

_ALD_InvInc_ec_rt.description: Decimal fraction of investment income base that can be excluded from AGI.
_ALD_InvInc_ec_rt.notes: The final taxable investment income will be (1-_ALD_InvInc_ec_rt)*investment_income_base. Even though the excluded portion of investment income is not included in AGI, it still is included in investment income used to calculate the Net Investment Income Tax and Earned Income Tax Credit.
_ALD_InvInc_ec_rt.title: Investment income exclusion rate haircut

_ALD_Dependents_hc.description: This decimal fraction, if greater than zero, reduces the portion of childcare costs that can be deducted from AGI.
_ALD_Dependents_hc.title: Deduction for childcare costs haircut

_ALD_Dependents_Child_c.description: The weighted average of childcare costs in the US. 7165 is the weighted average from the 'Child Care in America: 2016 State Fact Sheets'.
_ALD_Dependents_Child_c.notes: This is a weighted average of childcare costs in each state
_ALD_Dependents_Child_c.title: National average childcare costs: ceiling for available childcare deduction.

_ALD_Dependents_Elder_c.description: A taxpayer can take an above the line deduction up to this amount if they have an elderly dependent. The Trump 2016 campaign proposal was for $5000.
_ALD_Dependents_Elder_c.title: Ceiling for elderly care deduction proposed in Trump's tax plan

_ALD_Dependents_thd.description: A taxpayer can only claim the dependent care deduction if their total income is below this level. The Trump 2016 campaign proposal was for 250000 single, 500000 joint, 250000 separate, 500000 headhousehold].
_ALD_Dependents_thd.title: Maximum level of income to qualify for the dependent care deduction

_ALD_BusinessLosses_c.description: Business losses in excess of this amount may not be deducted from AGI.
_ALD_BusinessLosses_c.title: Maximum amount of business losses deductible

_II_em.description: Subtracted from AGI in the calculation of taxable income, per taxpayer and dependent.
_II_em.title: Personal and dependent exemption amount

_II_em_ps.description: If taxpayers' AGI is above this level, their personal exemption will start to decrease at the personal exemption phaseout rate (PEP provision).
_II_em_ps.title: Personal exemption phaseout starting income

_II_prt.description: Personal exemption amount will decrease by this rate for each dollar of AGI exceeding exemption phaseout start.
_II_prt.title: Personal exemption phaseout rate

_II_no_em_nu18.description: Total personal exemptions will be decreased by the number of dependents under the age of 18.
_II_no_em_nu18.title: Repeal personal exemptions for dependents under age 18

_STD.description: Amount filing unit can use as a standard deduction.
_STD.title: Standard deduction amount

_STD_Dep.description: This is the maximum standard deduction for dependents.
_STD_Dep.title: Standard deduction for dependents

_STD_Aged.description: To get the standard deduction for aged or blind individuals, taxpayers need to add this value to regular standard deduction.
_STD_Aged.section_2: Additional Standard Deduction For Blind And Aged
_STD_Aged.irs_ref: Form 1040, line 8, calculation (the difference of the two tables given in the instruction).
_STD_Aged.title: Additional standard deduction for blind and aged

_STD_allow_charity_ded_nonitemizers.description: Extends the charitable contributions deduction to taxpayers who take the standard deduction. The same ceilings, floor, and haircuts applied to itemized deduction for charitable contributions also apply here.
_STD_allow_charity_ded_nonitemizers.title: Allow standard deduction filers to take the charitable contributions deduction

_II_credit.description: This credit amount is fully refundable and is phased out based on AGI. It is available to tax units who would otherwise not file.
_II_credit.title: Personal refundable credit maximum amount

_II_credit_ps.description: The personal refundable credit amount will be reduced for taxpayers with AGI higher than this threshold level.
_II_credit_ps.title: Personal refundable credit phaseout start

_II_credit_prt.description: The personal refundable credit amount will be reduced at this rate for each dollar of AGI exceeding the _II_credit_ps threshold.
_II_credit_prt.title: Personal refundable credit phaseout rate

_II_credit_nr.description: This credit amount is not refundable and is phased out based on AGI.
_II_credit_nr.title: Personal nonrefundable credit maximum amount

_II_credit_nr_ps.description: The personal nonrefundable credit amount will be reduced for taxpayers with AGI higher than this threshold level.
_II_credit_nr_ps.title: Personal nonrefundable credit phaseout start

_II_credit_nr_prt.description: The personal nonrefundable credit amount will be reduced at this rate for each dollar of AGI exceeding the _II_credit_nr_ps threshold.
_II_credit_nr_prt.title: Personal nonrefundable credit phaseout rate

_ID_Medical_frt.description: Taxpayers are eligible to deduct the portion of their medical expenses exceeding this fraction of AGI.
_ID_Medical_frt.notes: When using PUF data, lowering this parameter value may produce unexpected results because PUF e17500 variable is zero below the floor.
_ID_Medical_frt.title: Floor (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for deductible medical expenses.

_ID_Medical_frt_add4aged.description: Elderly taxpayers have this fraction added to the value of the regular floor rate for deductible medical expenses.  This fraction was -0.025 from 2013 to 2016, but that was temporary and it changed to zero beginning in 2017.
_ID_Medical_frt_add4aged.notes: When using PUF data, changing this parameter value may produce unexpected results because PUF e17500 variable is zero below the floor.
_ID_Medical_frt_add4aged.title: Addon floor (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for deductible medical expenses for elderly filing units.

_ID_Medical_hc.description: This decimal fraction can be applied to limit the amount of medical expense deduction allowed.
_ID_Medical_hc.title: Medical expense deduction haircut

_ID_Medical_c.description: The amount of medical expense deduction is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_Medical_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of medical expense deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_StateLocalTax_hc.description: This decimal fraction reduces the state and local income and sales tax deduction.
_ID_StateLocalTax_hc.section_2: State And Local Income And Sales Taxes
_ID_StateLocalTax_hc.title: State and local income and sales taxes deduction haircut.

_ID_StateLocalTax_crt.description: The total deduction for state and local taxes is capped at this fraction of AGI.
_ID_StateLocalTax_crt.section_2: State And Local Income And Sales Taxes
_ID_StateLocalTax_crt.title: Ceiling (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for the combination of all state and local income and sales tax deductions.

_ID_StateLocalTax_c.description: The amount of state and local income and sales taxes deduction is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_StateLocalTax_c.section_2: State And Local Income And Sales Taxes
_ID_StateLocalTax_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of state and local income and sales taxes deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_RealEstate_hc.description: This decimal fraction reduces real estate taxes paid eligible to deduct in itemized deduction.
_ID_RealEstate_hc.section_2: State, Local, And Foreign Real Estate Taxes
_ID_RealEstate_hc.title: State, local, and foreign real estate taxes deduction haircut.

_ID_RealEstate_crt.description: The total deduction for all real estate taxes is capped at this fraction of AGI.
_ID_RealEstate_crt.section_2: State, Local, And Foreign Real Estate Taxes
_ID_RealEstate_crt.title: Ceiling (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for the combination of all state, local, and foreign real estate tax deductions.

_ID_RealEstate_c.description: The amount of real estate taxes deduction is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_RealEstate_c.section_2: State, Local, And Foreign Real Estate Taxes
_ID_RealEstate_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of state, local, and foreign real estate taxes deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_AllTaxes_hc.description: This decimal fraction reduces all state and local taxes paid eligible to deduct in itemized deduction.
_ID_AllTaxes_hc.section_2: State And Local Taxes And Real Estate Taxes
_ID_AllTaxes_hc.title: State and local income, sales, and real estate tax deduction haircut.

_ID_AllTaxes_c.description: The amount of state and local income, sales and real estate tax deductions is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_AllTaxes_c.section_2: State And Local Taxes And Real Estate Taxes
_ID_AllTaxes_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of state and local income, sales and real estate tax deductions allowed (dollars)

_ID_InterestPaid_hc.description: This decimal fraction can be applied to limit the amount of interest paid deduction allowed.
_ID_InterestPaid_hc.title: Interest paid deduction haircut

_ID_InterestPaid_c.description: The amount of interest paid deduction is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_InterestPaid_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of interest paid deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_Charity_crt_all.description: The total deduction for charity is capped at this fraction of AGI.
_ID_Charity_crt_all.irs_ref: Pub. 526, Limits on Deductions: 50% Limit Organizations.
_ID_Charity_crt_all.notes: When using PUF data, raising this parameter value may produce unexpected results because in PUF data the variables e19800 and e20100 are already capped.
_ID_Charity_crt_all.title: Ceiling (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for all charitable contribution deductions

_ID_Charity_crt_noncash.description: The deduction for noncash charity contributions is capped at this fraction of AGI.
_ID_Charity_crt_noncash.irs_ref: Pub 526, Limits on Deductions: Special 30% Limit for Capital Gain Property.
_ID_Charity_crt_noncash.notes: When using PUF data, raising this parameter value may produce unexpected results because in PUF data the variables e19800 and e20100 are already capped.
_ID_Charity_crt_noncash.title: Ceiling (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for noncash charitable contribution deductions

_ID_Charity_frt.description: Taxpayers are eligible to deduct the portion of their charitable expense exceeding this fraction of AGI.
_ID_Charity_frt.notes: This parameter allows for implementation of Option 52 from https://www.cbo.gov/sites/default/files/cbofiles/attachments/49638-BudgetOptions.pdf.
_ID_Charity_frt.title: Floor (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for deductible charitable contributions.

_ID_Charity_hc.description: This decimal fraction can be applied to limit the amount of charity expense deduction allowed.
_ID_Charity_hc.title: Charity expense deduction haircut

_ID_Charity_c.description: The amount of charity expense deduction is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_Charity_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of charity expense deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_Charity_f.description: Only charitable giving in excess of this dollar amount is eligible for a deduction.
_ID_Charity_f.title: Floor on the amount of charity expense deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_Casualty_frt.description: Taxpayers are eligible to deduct the portion of their gross casualty losses exceeding this fraction of AGI.
_ID_Casualty_frt.title: Floor (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for deductible casualty loss.

_ID_Casualty_hc.description: This decimal fraction can be applied to limit the amount of casualty expense deduction allowed.
_ID_Casualty_hc.title: Casualty expense deduction haircut

_ID_Casualty_c.description: The amount of casualty expense deduction is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_Casualty_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of casualty expense deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_Miscellaneous_frt.description: Taxpayers are eligible to deduct the portion of their miscellaneous expense exceeding this fraction of AGI.
_ID_Miscellaneous_frt.notes: When using PUF data, lowering this parameter value may produce unexpected results because in PUF data the variable e20400 is zero below the floor.
_ID_Miscellaneous_frt.title: Floor (as a decimal fraction of AGI) for deductible miscellaneous expenses.

_ID_Miscellaneous_hc.description: This decimal fraction can be applied to limit the amount of miscellaneous expense deduction allowed.
_ID_Miscellaneous_hc.title: Miscellaneous expense deduction haircut

_ID_Miscellaneous_c.description: The amount of miscellaneous expense deduction is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_Miscellaneous_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of miscellaneous expense deduction allowed (dollars)

_ID_ps.description: The itemized deductions will be reduced for taxpayers with AGI higher than this level.
_ID_ps.title: Itemized deduction phaseout AGI start (Pease provision)

_ID_prt.description: Taxpayers will not be eligible to deduct the full amount of itemized deduction if their AGI is above the phaseout start. The deductible portion would be decreased at this rate for each dollar exceeding the start.
_ID_prt.notes: This phaseout rate cannot be lower than 0.03 for each dollar, due to limited data on non-itemizers.
_ID_prt.title: Itemized deduction phaseout rate (Pease provision)

_ID_crt.description: The phaseout amount is capped at this fraction of the original total deduction.
_ID_crt.title: Itemized deduction maximum phaseout as a decimal fraction of total itemized deductions (Pease provision)

_ID_BenefitSurtax_trt.description: The benefit from specified itemized deductions exceeding the credit is taxed at this rate. A surtax rate of 1 strictly limits the benefit from specified itemized deductions to the specified credit. In http://www.nber.org/papers/w16921, Feldstein, Feenberg, and MacGuineas propose a credit of 2% of AGI against a 100% tax rate; in their proposal, however, a broader set of tax benefits, including the employer provided health exclusion, would be taxed.
_ID_BenefitSurtax_trt.section_2: Surtax On Itemized Deduction Benefits Above An AGI Threshold
_ID_BenefitSurtax_trt.title: Surtax rate on the benefits from specified itemized deductions

_ID_BenefitSurtax_crt.description: The surtax on specified itemized deductions applies to benefits in excess of this fraction of AGI. In http://www.nber.org/papers/w16921, Feldstein, Feenberg, and MacGuineas propose a credit of 2% of AGI against a 100% tax rate; in their proposal, however, a broader set of tax benefits, including the employer provided health exclusion, would be taxed.
_ID_BenefitSurtax_crt.section_2: Surtax On Itemized Deduction Benefits Above An AGI Threshold
_ID_BenefitSurtax_crt.title: Credit on itemized deduction benefit surtax (decimal fraction of AGI)

_ID_BenefitSurtax_em.description: This amount is subtracted from itemized deduction benefits in the calculation of the itemized deduction benefit surtax. With _ID_BenefitSurtax_crt set to 0.0 and _ID_BenefitSurtax_trt set to 1.0, this amount serves as a dollar limit on the value of itemized deductions.
_ID_BenefitSurtax_em.section_2: Surtax On Itemized Deduction Benefits Above An AGI Threshold
_ID_BenefitSurtax_em.title: Exemption for itemized deduction benefit surtax (dollar AGI threshold)

_ID_BenefitSurtax_Switch.description: The surtax on itemized deduction benefits applies to the benefits derived from the itemized deductions specified with this parameter.
_ID_BenefitSurtax_Switch.section_2: Surtax On Itemized Deduction Benefits Above An AGI Threshold
_ID_BenefitSurtax_Switch.title: Deductions subject to the surtax on itemized deduction benefits

_ID_BenefitCap_rt.description: The benefit from specified itemized deductions is capped at this percent of the total deductible expenses.
_ID_BenefitCap_rt.section_2: Ceiling On The Benefit Of Itemized Deductions As A Percent Of Deductible Expenses
_ID_BenefitCap_rt.title: Ceiling on the benefits from itemized deductions; decimal fraction of total deductible expenses

_ID_BenefitCap_Switch.description: The cap on itemized deduction benefits applies to the benefits derived from the itemized deductions specified with this parameter.
_ID_BenefitCap_Switch.section_2: Ceiling On The Benefit Of Itemized Deductions As A Percent Of Deductible Expenses
_ID_BenefitCap_Switch.title: Deductions subject to the cap on itemized deduction benefits

_ID_c.description: The amount of itemized deductions is limited to this dollar amount.
_ID_c.section_2: Ceiling On The Amount Of Itemized Deductions Allowed
_ID_c.title: Ceiling on the amount of itemized deductions allowed (dollars)

_ID_AmountCap_rt.description: The gross allowable amount of specified itemized deductions is capped at this percent of AGI.
_ID_AmountCap_rt.section_2: Ceiling On The Amount Of Itemized Deductions Allowed
_ID_AmountCap_rt.title: Ceiling on the gross amount of itemized deductions allowed; decimal fraction of AGI

_ID_AmountCap_Switch.description: The cap on itemized deduction benefits applies to the benefits derived from the itemized deductions specified with this parameter.
_ID_AmountCap_Switch.section_2: Ceiling On The Amount Of Itemized Deductions Allowed
_ID_AmountCap_Switch.title: Deductions subject to the cap on itemized deduction benefits

_CG_rt1.description: The capital gain and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) that are below threshold 1 are taxed at this rate.
_CG_rt1.section_2: Regular - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_CG_rt1.irs_ref: Form 1040 Schedule D tax worksheet, line 20, in-line.
_CG_rt1.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (regular/non-AMT) rate 1

_CG_brk1.description: The gains and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) below this are taxed at capital gain rate 1.
_CG_brk1.section_2: Regular - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_CG_brk1.irs_ref: Form 1040 Schedule D tax worksheet, line 15, in-line.
_CG_brk1.title: Top of long-term capital gains and qualified dividends (regular/non-AMT) tax bracket 1

_CG_rt2.description: The capital gain and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) that are below threshold 2 and above threshold 1 are taxed at this rate.
_CG_rt2.section_2: Regular - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_CG_rt2.irs_ref: Form 1040 Schedule D tax worksheet, line 29, in-line.
_CG_rt2.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (regular/non-AMT) rate 2

_CG_brk2.description: The gains and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) below this and above top of bracket 1 are taxed at capital gain rate 2.
_CG_brk2.section_2: Regular - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_CG_brk2.irs_ref: Form 1040 Schedule D tax worksheet, line 24, in-line.
_CG_brk2.title: Top of long-term capital gains and qualified dividends (regular/non-AMT) tax bracket 2

_CG_rt3.description: The capital gain and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) that are above threshold 2 and below threshold 3 are taxed at this rate.
_CG_rt3.section_2: Regular - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_CG_rt3.irs_ref: Form 1040 Schedule D tax worksheet, line 32, in-line.
_CG_rt3.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (regular/non-AMT) rate 3

_CG_brk3.description: The gains and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) below this and above top of bracket 2 are taxed at the capital gain rate 3; above this they are taxed at capital gain rate 4.  Default value is essentially infinity.
_CG_brk3.section_2: Regular - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_CG_brk3.irs_ref: Form 1040 Schedule D tax worksheet, line 24, in-line.
_CG_brk3.title: Top of long-term capital gains and qualified dividend tax (regular/non-AMT) bracket 3

_CG_rt4.description: The capital gain and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) that are above threshold 3 are taxed at this rate.
_CG_rt4.section_2: Regular - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_CG_rt4.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (regular/non-AMT) rate 4

_AMT_CG_rt1.description: Capital gain and qualified dividends (stacked on top of regular income) below threshold 1 are taxed at this rate.
_AMT_CG_rt1.section_2: AMT - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_AMT_CG_rt1.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (AMT) rate 1

_AMT_CG_brk1.description: The gains and dividends, stacked last, of AMT taxable income below this are taxed at AMT capital gain rate 1.
_AMT_CG_brk1.section_2: AMT - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_AMT_CG_brk1.title: Top of long-term capital gains and qualified dividends (AMT) tax bracket 1

_AMT_CG_rt2.section_2: AMT - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_AMT_CG_rt2.description: Capital gain and qualified dividend (stacked on top of regular income) below threshold 2 and above threshold 1 are taxed at this rate.
_AMT_CG_rt2.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (AMT) rate 2

_AMT_CG_brk2.description: The gains and dividends, stacked last, of AMT taxable income below this threshold and above bracket 1 are taxed at AMT capital gain rate 2.
_AMT_CG_brk2.section_2: AMT - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_AMT_CG_brk2.title: Top of long-term capital gains and qualified dividends (AMT) tax bracket 2

_AMT_CG_rt3.description: The capital gain and qualified dividend (stacked on top of regular income) above threshold 2 and below threshold 3 are taxed at this rate.
_AMT_CG_rt3.section_2: AMT - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_AMT_CG_rt3.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (AMT) rate 3

_AMT_CG_brk3.description: The gains and dividends, stacked last, of AMT taxable income below this and above bracket 2 are taxed at capital gain rate 3; above thisthey are taxed at AMT capital gain rate 4.  Default value is essentially infinity.
_AMT_CG_brk3.section_2: AMT - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_AMT_CG_brk3.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (AMT) threshold 3

_AMT_CG_rt4.description: The capital gain and dividends (stacked on top of regular income) that are above threshold 3 are taxed at this rate.
_AMT_CG_rt4.section_2: AMT - Long Term Capital Gains And Qualified Dividends
_AMT_CG_rt4.title: Long term capital gain and qualified dividends (AMT) rate 4

_CG_nodiff.description: Specifies whether or not long term capital gains and qualified dividends are taxed like regular taxable income.
_CG_nodiff.section_2: Tax All Capital Gains And Dividends The Same As Regular Taxable Income
_CG_nodiff.irs_ref: Current-law value is zero implying different tax treatment in Schedule D and AMT; a value of one implies same tax treatment in both regular and alternative minimum tax rules, but the same treatment can differ for regular and AMT.
_CG_nodiff.title: Long term capital gains and qualified dividends taxed no differently than regular taxable income

_CG_ec.description: Positive value used only if long term capital gains and qualified dividends taxed no differently than regular taxable income.
_CG_ec.section_2: Tax All Capital Gains And Dividends The Same As Regular Taxable Income
_CG_ec.title: Dollar amount of all capital gains and qualified dividends that are excluded from AGI.

_CG_reinvest_ec_rt.description: Positive value used only if long term capital gains and qualified dividends taxed no differently than regular taxable income.  To limit the exclusion to capital gains and dividends invested within one year, set to statutory exclusion rate times the fraction of capital gains and qualified dividends in excess of the exclusion that are assumed to be reinvested within the year.
_CG_reinvest_ec_rt.section_2: Tax All Capital Gains And Dividends The Same As Regular Taxable Income
_CG_reinvest_ec_rt.title: Fraction of all capital gains and qualified dividends in excess of the dollar exclusion that are excluded from AGI.

_II_rt1.description: The lowest tax rate, applied to the portion of taxable income below tax bracket 1.
_II_rt1.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 1

_II_brk1.description: Taxable income below this threshold is taxed at tax rate 1.
_II_brk1.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax bracket (upper threshold) 1

_II_rt2.description: The second lowest tax rate, applied to the portion of taxable income below tax bracket 2 and above tax bracket 1.
_II_rt2.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 2

_II_brk2.description: Income below this threshold and above tax bracket 1 is taxed at tax rate 2.
_II_brk2.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax bracket (upper threshold) 2

_II_rt3.description: The third lowest tax rate, applied to the portion of taxable income below tax bracket 3 and above tax bracket 2.
_II_rt3.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 3

_II_brk3.description: Income below this threshold and above tax bracket 2 is taxed at tax rate 3.
_II_brk3.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax bracket (upper threshold) 3

_II_rt4.description: The tax rate applied to the portion of taxable income below tax bracket 4 and above tax bracket 3.
_II_rt4.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 4

_II_brk4.description: Income below this threshold and above tax bracket 3 is taxed at tax rate 4.
_II_brk4.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax bracket (upper threshold) 4

_II_rt5.description: The third highest tax rate, applied to the portion of taxable income below tax bracket 5 and above tax bracket 4.
_II_rt5.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 5

_II_brk5.description: Income below this threshold and above tax bracket 4 is taxed at tax rate 5.
_II_brk5.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax bracket (upper threshold) 5

_II_rt6.description: The second higher tax rate, applied to the portion of taxable income below tax bracket 6 and above tax bracket 5.
_II_rt6.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 6

_II_brk6.description: Income below this threshold and above tax bracket 5 is taxed at tax rate 6.
_II_brk6.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax bracket 6

_II_rt7.description: The tax rate applied to the portion of taxable income below tax bracket 7 and above tax bracket 6.
_II_rt7.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 7

_II_brk7.description: Income below this threshold and above tax bracket 6 is taxed at tax rate 7; income above this threshold is taxed at tax rate 8.  Default value is essentially infinity.
_II_brk7.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax bracket 7

_II_rt8.description: The tax rate applied to the portion of taxable income above tax bracket 7.
_II_rt8.title: Personal income (regular/non-AMT/non-pass-through) tax rate 8

_PT_rt1.description: The lowest tax rate, applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below tax bracket 1.
_PT_rt1.title: Pass-through income tax rate 1

_PT_brk1.description: Income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below this threshold is taxed at tax rate 1.
_PT_brk1.title: Pass-through income tax bracket (upper threshold) 1

_PT_rt2.description: The second lowest tax rate, applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below tax bracket 2 and above tax bracket 1.
_PT_rt2.title: Pass-through income tax rate 2

_PT_brk2.description: Income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below this threshold and above tax bracket 1 is taxed at tax rate 2.
_PT_brk2.title: Pass-through income tax bracket (upper threshold) 2

_PT_rt3.description: The third lowest tax rate, applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below tax bracket 3 and above tax bracket 2.
_PT_rt3.title: Pass-through income tax rate 3

_PT_brk3.description: Income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below this threshold and above tax bracket 2 is taxed at tax rate 3.
_PT_brk3.title: Pass-through income tax bracket (upper threshold) 3

_PT_rt4.description: The tax rate applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below tax bracket 4 and above tax bracket 3.
_PT_rt4.title: Pass-through income tax rate 4

_PT_brk4.description: Income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below this threshold and above tax bracket 3 is taxed at tax rate 4.
_PT_brk4.title: Pass-through income tax bracket (upper threshold) 4

_PT_rt5.description: The third highest tax rate, applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below tax bracket 5 and above tax bracket 4.
_PT_rt5.title: Pass-through income tax rate 5

_PT_brk5.description: Income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below this threshold and above tax bracket 4 is taxed at tax rate 5.
_PT_brk5.title: Pass-through income tax bracket (upper threshold) 5

_PT_rt6.description: The second higher tax rate, applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below tax bracket 6 and above tax bracket 5.
_PT_rt6.title: Pass-through income tax rate 6

_PT_brk6.description: Income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below this threshold and above tax bracket 5 is taxed at tax rate 6.
_PT_brk6.title: Pass-through income tax bracket (upper threshold) 6

_PT_rt7.description: The highest tax rate, applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below tax bracket 7 and above tax bracket 6.
_PT_rt7.title: Pass-through income tax rate 7

_PT_brk7.description: Income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations below this threshold and above tax bracket 6 is taxed at tax rate 7. Default value is essentially infinity.
_PT_brk7.title: Extra pass-through income tax bracket

_PT_rt8.description: The extra tax rate, applied to the portion of income from sole proprietorships, partnerships and S-corporations above the tax bracket 7.
_PT_rt8.title: Extra pass-through income tax rate

_PT_EligibleRate_active.description: Eligibility rate of active business income for separate pass-through rates.
_PT_EligibleRate_active.notes: Active business income defined as e00900 + e26270
_PT_EligibleRate_active.title: Share of active business income eligible for PT rate schedule

_PT_EligibleRate_passive.description: Eligibility rate of passive business income for separate pass-through rates.
_PT_EligibleRate_passive.notes: Passive business income defined as e02000 - e26270
_PT_EligibleRate_passive.title: Share of passive business income eligible for PT rate schedule

_PT_wages_active_income.description: Whether active business income eligibility base for PT schedule for includes wages.
_PT_wages_active_income.notes: Only applies if active business income is positive
_PT_wages_active_income.title: Wages included in (positive) active business income eligible for PT rates

_PT_top_stacking.description: Whether taxable income eligible for PT rate schedule is stacked on top of regular taxable income.
_PT_top_stacking.title: PT taxable income stacked on top of regular taxable income

_PT_excl_rt.description: Fraction of qualified business income excluded from taxable income.
_PT_excl_rt.title: Pass-through income exclusion rate

_PT_excl_wagelim_rt.description: If taxpayer has partnership/S-corporation income, the amount of business income excluded from taxable income may not exceed this fraction of wages.
_PT_excl_wagelim_rt.title: Wage limit rate on pass-through income exclusion

_PT_excl_wagelim_thd.description: If taxpayer has partnership/S-corporation income, the amount of business income excluded from taxable income is limited by wages if taxable income exceeds this threshold.
_PT_excl_wagelim_thd.title: Phase-in threshold of wage limit on pass-through income exclusion

_PT_excl_wagelim_prt.description: If taxpayer has partnership/S-corporation income, the wage limitation on the amount of business income excluded from taxable income is phased in at this rate.
_PT_excl_wagelim_prt.title: Phase-in rate of wage limit on pass-through income exclusion

_AMT_em.description: The amount of AMT taxable income exempted from AMT.
_AMT_em.title: AMT exemption amount

_AMT_prt.description: AMT exemption will decrease at this rate for each dollar of AMT taxable income exceeding AMT phaseout start.
_AMT_prt.title: AMT exemption phaseout rate

_AMT_em_ps.description: AMT exemption starts to decrease when AMT taxable income goes beyond this threshold.
_AMT_em_ps.title: AMT exemption phaseout start

_AMT_child_em.description: The child's AMT exemption is capped by this amount plus the child's earned income.
_AMT_child_em.title: Child AMT exemption additional income base

_AMT_child_em_c_age.description: Individuals under this age must use the child AMT exemption rules.
_AMT_child_em_c_age.title: Age ceiling for special AMT exemption

_AMT_rt1.description: The tax rate applied to the portion of AMT taxable income below the surtax threshold, AMT bracket 1.
_AMT_rt1.title: AMT rate 1

_AMT_brk1.description: AMT taxable income below this is subject to AMT rate 1 and above it is subject to AMT rate 1 + the additional AMT rate.
_AMT_brk1.title: AMT bracket 1 (upper threshold)

_AMT_rt2.description: The additional tax rate applied to the portion of AMT income above the AMT bracket 1.
_AMT_rt2.notes: This is the additional tax rate (on top of AMT rate 1) for AMT income above AMT bracket 1.
_AMT_rt2.title: Additional AMT rate for AMT taxable income above AMT bracket 1

_AMT_em_pe.description: The AMT exemption is entirely disallowed beyond this AMT taxable income level for individuals who are married but filing separately.
_AMT_em_pe.title: AMT exemption phaseout ending AMT taxable income for Married filling Separately

_CDCC_c.description: The maximum amount of credit allowed for each qualifying dependent.
_CDCC_c.title: Maximum child & dependent care credit per dependent

_CDCC_ps.description: For taxpayers with AGI over this amount, the credit is reduced by one percentage point each $2000 of AGI over this amount.
_CDCC_ps.title: Child & dependent care credit phaseout start

_CDCC_crt.description: The maximum percentage rate in the AGI phaseout; this percentage rate decreases as AGI rises above the _CDCC_ps level.
_CDCC_crt.title: Child & dependent care credit phaseout percentage rate ceiling

_CTC_c.description: The maximum nonrefundable credit allowed for each child.
_CTC_c.title: Maximum nonrefundable child tax credit per child

_CTC_c_under5_bonus.description: The maximum amount of child tax credit allowed for each child is increased by this amount for qualifying children under 5 years old.
_CTC_c_under5_bonus.title: Bonus child tax credit maximum for qualifying children under five

_CTC_ps.description: Child tax credit begins to decrease when MAGI is above this level; read descriptions of the dependent credit amounts for how they phase out when MAGI is above this level.
_CTC_ps.title: Child tax credit phaseout MAGI start

_CTC_prt.description: The amount of the credit starts to decrease at this rate if MAGI is higher than child tax credit phaseout start.
_CTC_prt.irs_ref: Form 1040, line 12, instruction (child tax credit worksheet, line 7)
_CTC_prt.title: Child and dependent tax credit phaseout rate

_ACTC_c.description: This refundable credit is applied to child dependents and phases out exactly like the CTC amount.
_ACTC_c.title: Maximum refundable additional child tax credit

_ODC_c.description: This nonrefundable credit is applied to non-child dependents and phases out along with the CTC amount.
_ODC_c.irs_ref: Form 1040, line 12, instruction (child tax credit worksheet, line 2)
_ODC_c.notes: Became current-law policy with passage of TCJA
_ODC_c.title: Maximum nonrefundable other-dependent credit

_NIIT_thd.description: If modified AGI is more than this threshold, filing unit is subject to the Net Investment Income Tax.
_NIIT_thd.title: Net Investment Income Tax modified AGI threshold

_NIIT_PT_taxed.description: false ==> partnership and S-corp income excluded from NIIT base; true ==> partnership and S-corp income is in NIIT base.
_NIIT_PT_taxed.title: Whether or not partnership and S-corp income is in NIIT base

_NIIT_rt.description: If modified AGI exceeds _NIIT_thd, all net investment income is taxed at this rate.
_NIIT_rt.title: Net Investment Income Tax rate

_EITC_c.description: This is the maximum amount of earned income credit taxpayers are eligible for; it depends on how many kids they have.
_EITC_c.title: Maximum earned income credit

_EITC_rt.description: Pre-phaseout credit is minimum of this rate times earnings and the maximum earned income credit.
_EITC_rt.title: Earned income credit phasein rate

_EITC_basic_frac.description: This fraction of _EITC_c is always paid as a credit and one minus this fraction is applied to the phasein rate, _EITC_rt.  This fraction is zero under current law.
_EITC_basic_frac.title: Fraction of maximum earned income credit paid at zero earnings

_EITC_prt.description: Earned income credit begins to decrease at the this rate when AGI is higher than earned income credit phaseout start AGI.
_EITC_prt.title: Earned income credit phaseout rate

_EITC_ps.description: If AGI is higher than this threshold, the amount of EITC will start to decrease at the phaseout rate.
_EITC_ps.title: Earned income credit phaseout start AGI

_EITC_ps_MarriedJ.description: This is the additional amount added on the regular phaseout start amount for taxpayers with filling status of married filling jointly.
_EITC_ps_MarriedJ.irs_ref: Form 1040, line 17, calculation (the difference between EIC phaseout bases of married jointly fillers and other fillers).
_EITC_ps_MarriedJ.title: Extra earned income credit phaseout start AGI for married filling jointly

_EITC_MinEligAge.description: For a childless filling unit, at least one individual's age needs to be no less than this age (but no greater than the EITC_MaxEligAge) in order to be eligible for an earned income tax credit.
_EITC_MinEligAge.title: Minimum Age for Childless EITC Eligibility

_EITC_MaxEligAge.description: For a childless filling unit, at least one individual's age needs to be no greater than this age (but no less than the EITC_MinEligAge) in order to be eligible for an earned income tax credit.
_EITC_MaxEligAge.title: Maximum Age for Childless EITC Eligibility

_EITC_InvestIncome_c.description: The EITC amount is reduced when investment income exceeds this ceiling.
_EITC_InvestIncome_c.title: Maximum investment income before EITC reduction

_EITC_excess_InvestIncome_rt.description: The EITC amount is reduced at this rate per dollar of investment income exceeding the ceiling.
_EITC_excess_InvestIncome_rt.title: Rate of EITC reduction when investment income exceeds ceiling

_EITC_indiv.description: Current-law value is false implying EITC is filing-unit based; a value of true implies EITC is computed for each individual wage earner.  The phase-out of the credit works slightly differently between the two.  Individual-based calculation ignore investment income and age eligibilty rules used in filing-unit-based calculations.
_EITC_indiv.title: EITC is individual-based rather than filing-unit based

_LLC_Expense_c.description: The maximum expense eligible for lifetime learning credit, per child.
_LLC_Expense_c.title: Lifetime learning credit expense limit

_ETC_pe_Single.description: The education tax credit will be zero for those taxpayers of single filing status with modified AGI (in thousands) higher than this level.
_ETC_pe_Single.title: Education tax credit phaseout ends (Single)

_ETC_pe_Married.description: The education tax credit will be zero for those taxpayers of married filing status with modified AGI level (in thousands) higher than this level.
_ETC_pe_Married.title: Education tax credit phaseout ends (Married)

_ACTC_rt.description: This is the fraction of earnings used in calculating the ACTC, which is a partially refundable credit that supplements the CTC for some taxpayers.
_ACTC_rt.title: Additional Child Tax Credit rate

_ACTC_rt_bonus_under5family.description: For families with qualifying children under 5 years old, this bonus rate is added to the fraction of earnings (additional child tax credit rate) used in calculating the ACTC.
_ACTC_rt_bonus_under5family.title: Bonus additional child tax credit rate for families with qualifying children under 5

_ACTC_Income_thd.description: The portion of earned income below this threshold does not count as base for the Additional Child Tax Credit.
_ACTC_Income_thd.title: Additional Child Tax Credit income threshold

_ACTC_ChildNum.description: Families with this number of qualified children or more may qualify for a different formula to calculate the Additional Child Tax Credit, which is a partially refundable credit that supplements the Child Tax Credit for some taxpayers.
_ACTC_ChildNum.title: Additional Child Tax Credit minimum number of qualified children for different formula

_CTC_new_c.description: In addition to all credits currently available for dependents, this parameter gives each qualifying child a new refundable credit with this maximum amount.
_CTC_new_c.notes: Child age qualification for the new child tax credit is the same as under current-law Child Tax Credit.
_CTC_new_c.title: New refundable child tax credit maximum amount per child

_CTC_new_c_under5_bonus.description: The maximum amount of the new refundable child tax credit allowed for each child is increased by this amount for qualifying children under 5 years old.
_CTC_new_c_under5_bonus.title: Bonus new refundable child tax credit maximum for qualifying children under five

_CTC_new_for_all.description: The maximum amount of the new refundable child tax credit does not depend on AGI when true; otherwise, see _CTC_new_rt.
_CTC_new_for_all.title: Whether or not maximum amount of the new refundable child tax credit is available to all

_CTC_new_rt.description: The maximum amount of the new child tax credit is increased at this rate per dollar of positive AGI until _CTC_new_c times the number of qualified children is reached if CTC_new_for_all is false; if CTC_new_for_all is true, there is no AGI limitation to the maximum amount.
_CTC_new_rt.notes: Child age qualification for the new child tax credit is the same as under current-law Child Tax Credit.
_CTC_new_rt.title: New refundable child tax credit amount phasein rate

_CTC_new_ps.description: The total amount of new child tax credit is reduced for taxpayers with AGI higher than this level.
_CTC_new_ps.title: New refundable child tax credit phaseout starting AGI

_CTC_new_prt.description: The total amount of the new child tax credit is reduced at this rate per dollar exceeding the phaseout starting AGI, _CTC_new_ps.
_CTC_new_prt.title: New refundable child tax credit amount phaseout rate

_CTC_new_refund_limited.description: Specifies whether the new child tax credit refund is limited by the new child tax credit refund limit rate (_CTC_new_refund_limit_payroll_rt).
_CTC_new_refund_limited.notes: Set this parameter to true to limit the refundability or false to allow full refundability for all taxpayers.
_CTC_new_refund_limited.title: New child tax credit refund limited to a decimal fraction of payroll taxes

_CTC_new_refund_limit_payroll_rt.description: The fraction of payroll taxes (employee plus employer shares, but excluding all Medicare payroll taxes) that serves as a limit to the amount of new child tax credit that can be refunded.
_CTC_new_refund_limit_payroll_rt.notes: Set this parameter to zero for no refundability; set it to 9e99 for unlimited refundability for taxpayers with payroll tax liabilities.
_CTC_new_refund_limit_payroll_rt.title: New child tax credit refund limit rate (decimal fraction of payroll taxes)

_CTC_new_refund_limited_all_payroll.description: Specifies whether the new child tax credit refund limit rate (_CTC_new_refund_limit_payroll_rt) applies to all FICA taxes (true) or just OASDI taxes (false).
_CTC_new_refund_limited_all_payroll.notes: If the new CTC is limited, set this parameter to true to limit the refundability to all FICA taxes or false to limit refundabiity to OASDI taxes.
_CTC_new_refund_limited_all_payroll.title: New child tax credit refund limit applies to all FICA taxes, not just OASDI

_FST_AGI_trt.description: Individual income taxes and the employee share of payroll taxes are credited against this minimum tax, so the surtax is the difference between the tax rate times AGI and the credited taxes. The new minimum tax is similar to the Fair Share Tax, except that no credits are exempted from the base.
_FST_AGI_trt.title: New minimum tax; rate as a decimal fraction of AGI

_FST_AGI_thd_lo.description: A taxpayer is only subject to the new minimum tax if they exceed this level of AGI.
_FST_AGI_thd_lo.title: Minimum AGI needed to be subject to the new minimum tax

_FST_AGI_thd_hi.description: The new minimum tax will be fully phased in at this level of AGI. If there is no phase-in, this upper threshold should be set equal to the lower AGI threshold.
_FST_AGI_thd_hi.title: AGI level at which the New Minimum Tax is fully phased in

_AGI_surtax_trt.description: The surtax rate is applied to the portion of Adjusted Gross Income above the AGI surtax threshold.
_AGI_surtax_trt.title: New AGI surtax rate

_AGI_surtax_thd.description: The aggregate gross income above this AGI surtax threshold is taxed at surtax rate on AGI.
_AGI_surtax_thd.title: Threshold for the new AGI surtax

_LST.description: The lump-sum tax is levied on every member of a tax filing unit. The lump-sum tax is included only in combined taxes; it is not included in income or payroll taxes.
_LST.title: Dollar amount of lump-sum tax

_UBI_u18.description: UBI benefit provided to people under 18.
_UBI_u18.title: UBI benefit for those under 18

_UBI_1820.description: UBI benefit provided to people 18-20 years of age.
_UBI_1820.title: UBI benefit for those 18 through 20

_UBI_21.description: UBI benefit provided to people 21 and over.
_UBI_21.title: UBI benefit for those 21 and over

_UBI_ecrt.description: One minus this fraction of UBI benefits are taxable and will be added to AGI.
_UBI_ecrt.title: Fraction of UBI benefits excluded from AGI

_CR_RetirementSavings_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of the retirement savings credit that can be claimed.
_CR_RetirementSavings_hc.title: Credit for retirement savings haircut

_CR_ForeignTax_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of the foreign tax credit that can be claimed.
_CR_ForeignTax_hc.title: Credit for foreign tax haircut

_CR_ResidentialEnergy_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of the residential energy credit that can be claimed.
_CR_ResidentialEnergy_hc.title: Credit for residential energy haircut

_CR_GeneralBusiness_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of the general business credit that can be claimed.
_CR_GeneralBusiness_hc.title: Credit for general business haircut

_CR_MinimumTax_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of the previous year minimum tax credit that can be claimed.
_CR_MinimumTax_hc.title: Credit for previous year minimum tax credit haircut

_CR_AmOppRefundable_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of the refundable American Opportunity credit that can be claimed.
_CR_AmOppRefundable_hc.title: Refundable portion of the American Opportunity Credit haircut

_CR_AmOppNonRefundable_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of the nonrefundable American Opportunity credit that can be claimed.
_CR_AmOppNonRefundable_hc.title: Nonrefundable portion of the American Opportunity Credit haircut

_CR_SchR_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of Schedule R credit that can be claimed.
_CR_SchR_hc.title: Schedule R Credit haircut

_CR_OtherCredits_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of other credit that can be claimed.
_CR_OtherCredits_hc.title: Other Credits haircut

_CR_Education_hc.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction reduces the portion of education credits that can be claimed.
_CR_Education_hc.title: Education Credits haircut

_CR_Charity_rt.description: If greater than zero, this decimal fraction represents the portion of total charitable contributions provided as a nonrefundable tax credit.
_CR_Charity_rt.title: Charity Credit rate

_CR_Charity_f.description: Only charitable giving in excess of this dollar amount is eligible for the charity credit.
_CR_Charity_f.title: Charity Credit Floor

_CR_Charity_frt.description: Only charitable giving in excess of this decimal fraction of AGI is eligible for the charity credit.
_CR_Charity_frt.title: Charity Credit Floor Rate

_BEN_ssi_repeal.description: SSI benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_ssi_repeal.title: SSI benefit repeal switch

_BEN_housing_repeal.description: Housing benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_housing_repeal.title: Housing benefit repeal switch

_BEN_snap_repeal.description: SNAP benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_snap_repeal.title: SNAP benefit repeal switch

_BEN_tanf_repeal.description: TANF benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_tanf_repeal.title: TANF benefit repeal switch

_BEN_vet_repeal.description: Veterans benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_vet_repeal.title: Veterans benefit repeal switch

_BEN_wic_repeal.description: WIC benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_wic_repeal.title: WIC benefit repeal switch

_BEN_mcare_repeal.description: Medicare benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_mcare_repeal.title: Medicare benefit repeal switch

_BEN_mcaid_repeal.description: Medicaid benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_mcaid_repeal.title: Medicaid benefit repeal switch

_BEN_oasdi_repeal.description: Social Security benefits (e02400) can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_oasdi_repeal.title: Social Security benefit repeal switch

_BEN_ui_repeal.description: Unemployment insurance benefits (e02300) can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_ui_repeal.title: Unemployment insurance benefit repeal switch

_BEN_other_repeal.description: Other benefits can be repealed by switching this parameter to true.
_BEN_other_repeal.title: Other benefit repeal switch
